Class Occurrence

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.netbeans.api.java.source.matching.Occurrence

  • public final class Occurrence
extends Object
    A found occurrence of a pattern.

    • Method Detail

      • getOccurrenceRoot

        public TreePath getOccurrenceRoot()
        The tree node that represents the occurrence. For multi-part patterns Pattern.createSimplePattern(java.lang.Iterable), returns the TreePath corresponding to the first part (TODO: verify!).
        Returns:
        root tree of the occurrence

      • getVariables

        public Map<String,TreePath> getVariables()
        For patterns with free variables, contains mapping of single-variable names to the tree node that was bound to the variable. That means, the tree node that corresponds to the first occurrence of the variable in the pattern.
        Returns:
        mapping of free variable names to the tree nodes that were bound to them

      • getMultiVariables

        public Map<String,Collection<? extends TreePath>> getMultiVariables()
        For patterns with free variables, contains mapping of multi-variable names to the tree nodes that were bound to the variable. That means, the tree nodes that corresponds to the first occurrence of the variable in the pattern.
        Returns:
        mapping of free variable names to the tree nodes that were bound to them

      • getVariables2Names

        public Map<String,String> getVariables2Names()
        For patterns with free variables, contains mapping of variable names to a name that was bound to the variable.
        Returns:
        mapping of free variable names to names that were bound to them

      • getVariablesRemapToElement

        public Map<Element,Element> getVariablesRemapToElement()
        For patterns which allow variable remap, contains mapping of the element in the pattern to the corresponding element in this occurrence.
        Returns:
        mapping of elements in the pattern to the elements in this occurrence

      • getVariablesRemapToTrees

        public Map<Element,TreePath> getVariablesRemapToTrees()
        For patterns which allow variable remap to trees, contains mapping of the element in the pattern to the corresponding tree node in this occurrence.
        Returns:
        mapping of elements in the pattern to the elements in this occurrence
